# Normalize line endings across platforms.
#
# Text files are stored in Git as LF and checked out as LF everywhere,
# overriding each contributor's core.autocrlf. On Windows (where
# autocrlf=true would otherwise leave CRLF in the working tree) this keeps
# the working copy LF, so Prettier's LF-based `format:check` stays in sync
# with what CI (Linux) sees instead of failing on line endings alone.
#
# `text=auto` still lets Git auto-detect text vs. binary; the explicit
# rules below keep binary assets safe regardless of that detection.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply EOL conversion.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
